Place @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small bowl{}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; halve crosswise. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored and thinly sliced into strips). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}(trimmed and thinly sliced, separating whites from greens). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Heat a #large dry pan{} over high heat. Add green beans, a small splash of water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook until green beans are lightly charred and water has evaporated, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir @Arborio rice{3/4%cup}, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, and @garlic powder{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) into pan with bell pepper and scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @water{3%cups} (6 cups for 4), @seafood stock concentrate{2}, and @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4). Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has evaporated and rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> TIP: If liquid evaporates before rice is tender, add a splash more water.

While rice cooks, in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine scallion greens, remaining @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until fragrant and sizzling, ~{30-45%seconds}. Uncover and set aside to cool.

Once scallion mixture has cooled, stir in @mayonnaise{6%tbsp} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

To bowl with softened butter, stir in lemon zest, @chili powder{1%tsp} (all for 4), and @sugar{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Pat @scallops{10%ounce} dry with paper towels.

When rice is almost done, heat a drizzle of oil in a second #large pan{} over high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and season with salt and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add scallops and season with salt and pepper; cook until everything is opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Stir in chili lemon butter and a big squeeze of lemon juice until melted and combined.

Once rice is tender, stir in @peas{4%ounce} and green beans. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Top with shrimp and scallops and drizzle with scallion aioli. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: Serve directly from pan for a family style paella experience!